I think a problem with talk about inerrancy of the Bible is that what prompts that sort of talk is some misunderstand the notion of inspiration. The idea of inspiration in the Bible is &quot;breath&quot;. Indead, the scriptures are &quot;God breathed&quot; according to one New Testament passage. Notice, this isn't automatic writing where god takes control of some poor soul and forces quill to parchment and ZAP scripture is written! The writers and editors of the pages of the Bible are inspired by the idea and concepts of their gods and write from that inspiration. Much like a painter paints on canvass inspired by a model or thought. <br>
<br>
Problems arise when the stories and symbols of the Bible are treated literally by those who don't understand the meaning of inspiration and begin to think of the Bible as a rule book and not as a guide.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwealthacquirer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wealth Acquirer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/20/01 4:36:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=192>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow</span><hr size=1> Please Muzaak, do not turn this into a question of understanding.  As many in here on both sides of the argument have shown that they are quite capable of understanding some rather heavy concepts.<br>
